{"title_page": "SOB X RBE", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = \n| image            = SOB_X_RBE_performing_in_Austin,_Texas_(2016-06-16).jpg\n| image_size       = 250px\n| image_upright    = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = SOB X RBE performing in June 2018\n| background       = group_or_band\n| alias            = Real Boi  Entertainment\n| Origin           = [[Vallejo, California]]\n| Genre            = {{hlist|[[West Coast hip hop]]|[[hyphy]]}}\n| Years_active     = {{Start date|2016}}\u2013present\n| Label            = [[Interscope Records|Interscope]], [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]]\n| associated_acts  = {{flatlist|\n*[[03 Greedo]]\n*Big Money x OBM\n*[[Hit-Boy]]\n*[[Shoreline Mafia]]\n*[[Marshmello]]}}\n| website          = {{URL|http://sobxrbe.com/}}\n| Current_members  = * Slimmy B\n* DaBoii\n* Yhung T.O.\n* Lul G (Not Active)\n}}\n\n'''SOB X RBE''' (an [[acronym]] of '''Strictly Only Brothers x Real Boi Entertainment''') is an American music group originating from [[Vallejo, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/sob-x-rbe-gangin/|title=SOB X RBE: Gangin Album Review|website=Pitchfork|language=en|access-date=2018-04-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180421031019/https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/sob-x-rbe-gangin/|archive-date=2018-04-21|url-status=live}}</ref> The group consists of three active members; Yhung T.O, DaBoii and Slimmy B. The group was founded in 2016 by, Slimmy B (Jabbar Brown), Yhung T.O. (Juwon Lee), DaBoii (Wayman Barrow), and Lul G (George Harris).<ref>{{cite web | title = SOB X RBE | url =https://music.apple.com/us/artist/sob-x-rbe/1192174117 | website = music.apple.com | access-date =22 January 2020 }}</ref> The group was formed during their teenage years and they worked together to create music.<ref>{{cite web | title = SOB X RBE | url =https://music.apple.com/us/artist/sob-x-rbe/1192174117 | website = music.apple.com | access-date =22 January 2020 }}</ref> Their sound is highly influenced by the Bay Area and various artist that make up the Hip- Hop and Rap culture of California.<ref>{{cite web | title = SOB X RBE | url =https://music.apple.com/us/artist/sob-x-rbe/1192174117 | website = music.apple.com | access-date =22 January 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== Music career ==\nAs SOB x RBE gained momentum and exposure, in 2017 they caught the eye of Bay Area rapper [[Sage the Gemini]] who took the group under apprenticeship and had them be the opening act for his tour.<ref>{{cite web | title = SOB X RBE | url =https://music.apple.com/us/artist/sob-x-rbe/1192174117 | website = music.apple.com | access-date =22 January 2020 }}</ref> He introduced the group to more prominent names in the music industry to help them gain more momentum.<ref>{{cite web | title = SOB X RBE | url =https://music.apple.com/us/artist/sob-x-rbe/1192174117 | website = music.apple.com | access-date =22 January 2020 }}</ref> The group has released six complete projects: a self-titled mixtape in 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/sob-x-rbe/1198398937|title=SOB X RBE by SOB X RBE on Apple Music|website=iTunes|accessdate=6 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180606083647/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/sob-x-rbe/1198398937|archive-date=6 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> a debut album ''Gangin'' in 2018, an EP with Big Money, a second album ''Gangin II'' in late 2018, an EP with Marshmello, and an album \"Family Not A Group\" with producer Hit Boy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/gangin-mw0003157792|title=Gangin - SOB X RBE - Songs, Reviews, Credits - AllMusic|website=AllMusic|accessdate=18 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718234642/https://www.allmusic.com/album/gangin-mw0003157792|archive-date=18 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The group found mainstream attention after being featured on the track \"Paramedic!\" for the 2018 superhero film ''[[Black Panther (film)|Black Panther]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/lyrics/8223821/sob-x-rbe-paramedic-lyrics-black-panther-kendrick-lamar |title=Here are the Lyrics to SOB x RBE's 'Paramedic!,' Feat. Kendrick Lamar |website=Billboard |access-date=2018-04-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524192129/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/lyrics/8223821/sob-x-rbe-paramedic-lyrics-black-panther-kendrick-lamar |archive-date=2018-05-24 |url-status=live }}</ref> The group has gone on multiple tours around the United States and have been interviewed multiple times by ''[[The Fader]]'' and [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefader.com/2017/04/26/sob-x-rbe-interview-slimmy-b-daboii-lul-g-yhung-to|title=A Raw Conversation With SOB x RBE, The Vallejo Boys Setting The Bay On Fire|website=The FADER|accessdate=23 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180429023003/http://www.thefader.com/2017/04/26/sob-x-rbe-interview-slimmy-b-daboii-lul-g-yhung-to|archive-date=29 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8214833/sob-x-rbe-interview-new-album-gangin-black-panther-soundtrack|title=SOB x RBE Talks New Album 'Gangin' & Working on 'Black Panther' Soundtrack With Kendrick Lamar|website=Billboard|accessdate=23 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fboV36_Pu6U|title=The SOB x RBE Interview Pt. 1 -- Thizzler.com Interview|first=|last=Thizzler On The Roof|date=1 March 2017|publisher=|accessdate=23 April 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Ivey |first=Justin |url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.48503/title.yhung-t-o-is-leaving-sob-x-rbe-after-gangin-2 |title=Yhung T.O To Exit SOB x RBE After \"Gangin 2\"Album |publisher=HipHopDX |date=2018-09-19 |accessdate=2019-11-06}}</ref> The group is currently not signed to any recording label but, certain members in the group are signed to record labels as solo independent recording artist.<ref>{{cite AV media| people = DJ Vlad| title =SOB X RBE: Slimmy B Robbed a House, Returned the Money 6 Months Later (Part 6)| medium = Youtube | publisher = VladTV}}</ref> They each have their own specific sound and history that makes them individuals and each group member has their own mixtapes and solo projects that they work on outside of the group.<ref>{{cite AV media| people = DJ Vlad| title =SOB X RBE: Slimmy B Robbed a House, Returned the Money 6 Months Later (Part 6)| medium = Youtube | publisher = VladTV}}</ref> In an interview with DJ Vlad the group disclosed that despite musical differences they will always remain a \"family\" before a musical group.<ref>{{cite AV media| people = DJ Vlad| title =SOB X RBE: Slimmy B Robbed a House, Returned the Money 6 Months Later (Part 6)| medium = Youtube | publisher = VladTV}}</ref>\n\n== Biographies ==\n'''Juwon Lee (Yhung T.O.)'''\n\nBorn on December 7, 1998 in Vallejo, California, Yhung T.O. has had a passion for making music since he was in middle school and essentially brought the group together as he was the one with the studio the men began recording their very first hits in.<ref>{{Citation|title=The SOB x RBE Interview Pt. 1 {{!}}{{!}} Thizzler.com Interview|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fboV36_Pu6U|language=en|access-date=2020-01-31}}</ref> SOB x RBE was a merge of two pre-existing groups, Real Boi Entertainment (RBE) was Yhung T.O.'s musical group, starting as early as ninth grade.<ref>{{Citation|title=SOB X RBE Speak On Being Underdog Black Rappers & Struggles As A Group From The Bay|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8sn92C4Sffs|language=en|access-date=2020-02-07}}</ref>  Yhung T.O. had gotten married at the age of nineteen and is still currently married.<ref>{{cite AV media| people = DJ Vlad| title =SOB X RBE: Slimmy B Robbed a House, Returned the Money 6 Months Later (Part 6)| medium = Youtube | publisher = VladTV}}</ref> In March 2018 Yhung T.O. revealed his signing to the record label [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]. A record label who acquired Dr. Dre's [[Death Row Records]] in the late 90's.Yhung T.O. was signed by [[Joie Manda]] in December 2017. The group expressed that they are still a family, though Yhung T.O. was signed as a solo artist to the label.<ref>{{cite AV media|people = DJ Vlad|title=SOB x RBE on Break-Up Rumors, Why Yhung T.O. Got a Solo Deal| medium = Vlad TV| publisher =VladTV}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kqed.org/arts/13828024/what-happens-to-sob-x-rbe-now-that-yhung-t-o-has-an-interscope-deal|title=What Happens to SOB x RBE Now That Yhung T.O. Has An Interscope Deal?|date=2018-03-27|website=KQED|language=en-us|access-date=2020-01-31}}</ref> His signing left fans with unanswered questions as to what is going to happen to the musical group in the long run.<ref>{{cite AV media| people = DJ Vlad| title =SOB X RBE: Slimmy B Robbed a House, Returned the Money 6 Months Later (Part 6)| medium = Youtube | publisher = VladTV}}</ref>\n\n'''Wayan Barrow (DaBoii)'''\n\nBorn on August 24, 1997 in Vallejo, California, DaBoii also was making music since he could remember and at a very young age joined Yhung T.O. in his studio where they began to make music.<ref>{{Citation|title=The SOB x RBE Interview Pt. 1 {{!}}{{!}} Thizzler.com Interview|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fboV36_Pu6U|language=en|access-date=2020-01-31}}</ref> The second half of the musical groups final merge was Strictly Only Brothers (SOB) and this was DaBoii's initial group.<ref>{{Citation|title=SOB X RBE Speak On Being Underdog Black Rappers & Struggles As A Group From The Bay|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8sn92C4Sffs|language=en|access-date=2020-02-07}}</ref> During an interview with the musical group, DaBoii revealed  that he is known to be the most soft-spoken among the three and keeps very quiet around those he does not know well.<ref>{{Citation|title=SOB x RBE on growing up in Vallejo, recruiting Swaggy P, and tour life|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DoHkoTmp6us|language=en|access-date=2020-01-31}}</ref> While the group is known for their collaborative music, each member identifies themselves as an independent artist, with DaBoii also taking steps to sign with a record label.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/featured/yhung-t-o-interview-profile/|title=Yhung T.O. Interview: Can He Be the Bay's New Star?|date=2019-03-28|website=Spin|access-date=2020-01-31}}</ref> In December 2019, DaBoii announced on Instagram he has a son.\n\n'''Jabbar Brown''' '''(Slimmy B)'''\n\nBorn on February 26, 1997 in Vallejo, California Slimmy B is the third active member of the musical group. Slimmy B's passion to pursue music also started very early on, just like the rest of the group. He attended Vallejo Middle School where he and DaBoii met and formed their relationship. In an interview, Slimmy B revealed that he had a son and before the group had gained exposure he was working at various wineries and warehouses in Vallejo, California to take care of his family.<ref>{{cite AV media| people = DJ Vlad| title =SOB X RBE: Slimmy B Robbed a House, Returned the Money 6 Months Later (Part 6)| medium = Youtube | publisher = VladTV}}</ref>  In an interview with the artists, it was revealed that among the three, Slimmy B seems to be the artist with all the jokes.<ref>{{Citation|title=SOB x RBE on growing up in Vallejo, recruiting Swaggy P, and tour life|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DoHkoTmp6us|language=en|access-date=2020-01-31}}</ref>\n\n'''George Harris (Lul G)'''\n\nBorn on November 14, 1998 in Vallejo, California Lul G is currently not an active member in the group as of late 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8531980/former-sob-x-rbe-rapper-lul-g-arrested-murderl|title=Former SOB x RBE Rapper Lul G Arrested for Murder|date=2019-02-10|website=Billboard|language=en-us|access-date=2020-01-31}}</ref> Lul G signed to Def Jam reccords in the summer of 2018 as a solo artist.<ref>{{cite web | title = Can Yhung T.O. Be the Bay\u2019s Pensive New Star?| url =https://www.spin.com/featured/yhung-t-o-interview-profile/| website = Spin |language=en-us| access-date =22 January 2020 }}</ref> KQUED, reported that the Fairfield Police Department, stated that a Lul G (George Harris) was charged for murder and arrested On September 21, 2019.<ref>{{cite web | title = Shooting Victim in Lul G's Murder Trial Was Close Friend of SOB x RBE| url =https://www.kqed.org/arts/13868326/sob-rbe-lul-g-murder-trial-arrest| website = KQUED |language=en-us| access-date =22 January 2020 }}</ref>\nHe is currently being held in the Stanton Correction Facility in Fairfield, California. Harris is being charged for Killing Rashield Flowers a friend to the SOB x RBE and co-worker.<ref>{{cite web | title = Shooting Victim in Lul G's Murder Trial Was Close Friend of SOB x RBE| url =https://www.kqed.org/arts/13868326/sob-rbe-lul-g-murder-trial-arrest| website = KQUED |language=en-us| access-date =22 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of studio albums, with selected chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-200/2018-03-10|title=Top 200 Albums|work=Billboard|accessdate=August 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180727220846/https://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-200/2018-03-10|archive-date=July 27, 2018|url-status=live}}\n* ''Gangin II'': {{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-200/2018-10-13|title=Top 200 Albums: October 13, 2018|work=Billboard|accessdate=October 9, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181009152410/https://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-200/2018-10-13|archive-date=October 9, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Gangin''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/gangin/1343900906|title=GANGIN by SOB X RBE|work=[[iTunes]]|accessdate=August 18, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180719024422/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/gangin/1343900906|archive-date=July 19, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: February 23, 2018\n* Label: [[Empire Distribution|Empire]]\n* Format: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| 74\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Gangin II''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/gangin-ii/1436537407|title=GANGIN II by SOB X RBE|work=[[iTunes]]|accessdate=October 1, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181002172506/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/gangin-ii/1436537407|archive-date=October 2, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: September 28, 2018\n* Label: Empire\n* Format: Digital download\n| 191\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Family Not a Group (with [[Hit-Boy]])''<ref>{{Citation|title=Family Not a Group by Hit-Boy & SOB X RBE|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/family-not-a-group/1458001289|language=en-us|access-date=2020-02-07}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: April 16, 2019\n* Label: [[Def Jam]] \n* Format: Digital download\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Strictly Only Brothers''<ref>{{Citation|title=Strictly Only Brothers by SOB X RBE|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/strictly-only-brothers/1491225607|language=en-us|access-date=2020-02-07}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: December 20, 2019\n* Label: Empire\n* Format: Digital download\n|\n|}\n\n===Mixtapes===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of mixtapes, with selected details\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''SOB X RBE''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/sob-x-rbe/1198398937