]]\n* [[Jopie Nooren]]\n* [[Mohamed Sini]]\n* [[Andr\u00e9 Postema]]\n* [[Lambert Verheijen]]\n* [[Janny Vlietstra]]\n* [[Wouter van Zandbrink]]\n\n===Members of the European Parliament===\nCurrent members of the [[European Parliament]] since the [[2019 European Parliament election|European Parliamentary election of 2019]] (four women, two men):\n{{further|2019 European Parliament election in the Netherlands}} \n{{further|List of members of the European Parliament for the Netherlands, 2019\u201324}}\n{{further|Party lists in the 2019 European Parliament election in the Netherlands#P.v.d.A./European Social Democrats}}\n6 seats: \n# [[Agnes Jongerius]]\n# [[Kati Piri]]\n# [[Paul Tang (politician)|Paul Tang]]\n# [[Vera Tax]]\n# [[Mohammed Chahim]]\n# [[Lara Wolters]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* Orlow, Dietrich. ''Common Destiny: A Comparative History of the Dutch, French, and German Social Democratic Parties, 1945\u20131969'' (2000) [https://www.questia.com/read/110575026/common-destiny-a-comparative-history-of-the-dutch online]\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Partij van de Arbeid}}\n*{{Official website}} {{in lang|nl}}\n* PvdA archives at the [[International Institute of Social History]]: [http://hdl.handle.net/10622/COLL00160 Objectencollectie] * [http://hdl.handle.net/10622/ARCH01125 Archief]\n\n{{Dutch Political Parties}}\n{{Socialist parties in the Netherlands}}\n{{Party of European Socialists}}\n\n[[Category:Labour Party (Netherlands)| ]]\n[[Category:1946 establishments in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Former member parties of the Socialist International]]\n[[Category:Labour parties]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Amsterdam]]\n[[Category:Party of European Socialists member parties]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 1946]]\n[[Category:Political parties in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Social democratic parties]]\n[[Category:Social democratic parties in the Netherlands]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dat