'[[Party lists in the 2019 European Parliament election in the Netherlands#P.v.d.A./European Social Democrats|List]]'''\n| 1,045,274\n| 19.01% (#1)\n| {{Composition bar|6|26|hex={{Dutch Labour Party/meta/color}}}}\n| 3 {{increase}} \n| <ref name=\"historicEP2019results\">{{cite news|title=Kiesraad: Europees Parlement 23 mei 2019|url=https://www.verkiezingsuitslagen.nl/verkiezingen/detail/EP20190523|publisher=Kiesraad|date=4 June 2019|language=nl-NL|accessdate=19 June 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Representation==\n=== Members of the House of Representatives ===\nThe nine members (five men, four women) of the [[House of Representatives (Netherlands)|House of Representatives]] for the Labour Party are:<ref>\"[https://www.houseofrepresentatives.nl/parliamentary-parties/labour-party Labour party] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170325024540/https://www.houseofrepresentatives.nl/parliamentary-parties/labour-party |date=25 March 2017 }}\", ''[[House of Representatives (Netherlands)|House of Representatives]]''. Retrieved 24 March 2017.</ref>\n\n* '''[[Lodewijk Asscher]]''', [[parliamentary leader]]\n* [[Khadija Arib]], [[Speaker of the House of Representatives (Netherlands)|Speaker of the House]]\n* [[Gijs van Dijk]]\n* [[Kirsten van den Hul]]\n* [[John Kerstens]]\n* [[Attje Kuiken]]\n* [[William Moorlag]]\n* [[Henk Nijboer]]\n* [[Lilianne Ploumen]]\n\n===Members of the Senate===\nThe eight members (four men, four women) of the [[Senate (Netherlands)|Senate]] for the Labour Party are:<ref>\"[https://www.eerstekamer.nl/fractie/partij_van_de_arbeid PvdA-fractie] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170128173029/https://www.eerstekamer.nl/fractie/partij_van_de_arbeid |date=28 January 2017 }}\" (in Dutch), ''[[Senate (Netherlands)|Senate]]''. Retrieved 28 February 2018.</ref>\n\n* '''[[Esther-Mirjam Sent]]''', [[parliamentary leader]]\n* [[Jannette Beuving]]\n* [[Jopie Nooren]]\n* [[Mohamed Sini]]\n* [[Andr\u00e9 Postema]]\n* [[Lambert Verheijen]]\n* [[Janny 